{
  "stem": "25348.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So they recruited-- the Nazis recruited a lot of these men, allegedly, for work, but they've never-- about 3,000 of them-- and they never came back.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Whereas [NON-ENGLISH] Lampert-- that was my mother's husband.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I was very fond of him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I called him by the name, and not like-- I didn't call Father.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When they arrested him, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we tried, Mother and I, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to, to get him out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I don't know much.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I was only 14 at the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I don't know much about the bureaucratic setup.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But we went to the Judenrat, my mother and I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I remember the chairman of the Judenrat was a Jewish lawyer, called Pincus.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And my mother wanted to invest in her last piece of jewelry to bribe someone close to the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] administration to get him out.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I remember that he used to slip into the hands of Poles he was arrested little notes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "One said, my life hangs on a thin thread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "That's what I remember, but I've never seen him again.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "When the Germans came to Luck in December of the year that they arrived, 1941-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they arrived in June.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And what I'm telling you about the arrest of the young men was in July.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Within that break from July to December, they managed to organize a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They pushed all the Jews into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And that was December 1941.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there were terrible conditions in the ghetto, but [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you don't realize how inventive you can be, even when you're young.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
